"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455357","Department of Health","false","2016-03-01","<p>This information is not collected centrally. Prescribing information is not linked to the patient receiving the prescription so it is not possible to supply prescribing information by patient age.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-03-01T16:41:22.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455357/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455357/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-25","Prescription Drugs: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many children aged (a) up to 12, (b) 12 to 15 and (c) 16 to 18 were prescribed (i) fluoxetine, (ii) fluvoxamine, (iii) sertraline, (iv) paroxetine, (v) escitalopram and (vi) citalopra by the NHS in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","28593"
