"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455450","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-01","<p>The number of inbound calls received by the Child Maintenance Options Service from November 2015 is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Month</p></td><td><p>Number of calls received by the Child Maintenance Options Service</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nov-15</p></td><td><p>35,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec-15</p></td><td><p>29,600</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-16</p></td><td><p>49,700</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Data Sourced from Child Maintenance Options Monthly MI Service Pack.</li><li>Data rounded to nearest 100.</li></ol>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-01T15:30:34.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455450/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455450/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-25","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many calls were made to the Child Maintenance Options Service in each month since November 2015.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","28466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455451","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-04","<p>The Department’s records relating to the data requested are not comprehensive. Obtaining data that does exist would take the costs of responding to the question over the disproportionate cost threshold.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-03-04T12:20:48.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455451/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455451/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Human Rights Act 1998","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many civil law suits have been brought against his Department based either wholly or partially on grounds provided by the Human Rights Act 1998; how many such suits were settled out of court before a court judgment was delivered; and how much such settlements have cost the public purse since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455452","Department for Work and Pensions","true","2016-03-04","<p><del class="ministerial">This information is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</del></p><p><ins class="ministerial"><strong>As part of this Government’s transparency agenda, all Departments are required to publish monthly workforce statistics that includes overtime costs. This information is available from the gov.uk website at:</strong></ins></p><p><ins class="ministerial"> </ins></p><p><ins class="ministerial"><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-staff-numbers-and-associated-costs" target="_blank"><strong>https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-staff-numbers-and-associated-costs</strong></a></ins></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-03-04T12:27:44.173Z","2016-03-18T11:14:54.78Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455452/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455452/answer","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455452/answer/previousversion/49110","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Overtime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has paid to staff in overtime in each of the last 24 months.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","28696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455453","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-01","<p>The information as requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Published information available on Help to Work shows the number of programme referrals and Community Work Placement starts and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/help-to-work-quarterly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/help-to-work-quarterly-statistics</a><br></p><p>This covers the period from April 2014 (when the programme started) to September 2015 inclusive.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2016-03-01T16:02:08.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455453/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/455453/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-25","Help to Work Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many long-term unemployed people have been helped back into work through the Help to Work scheme in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","28589"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454637","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>It is not possible to answer the question as there is no agreed statistical definition of what is meant by the term “engineering sector”.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2016-03-02T15:50:58.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454637/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454637/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454637/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-24","Engineering: Migrant Workers","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many employees in the UK engineering sector are from other EU member states, and what is their total contribution to (1) UK Gross Domestic Product, and (2) UK Gross Value Added.","false","Biography information for Baroness Burt of Solihull",,"Baroness Burt of Solihull","HL6387"
