"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454641","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-02","<p>The review of the Code of Practice for the Welfare of Privately Kept Non-Human Primates is expected to commence this year with a view to recommendations being made within a year.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-03-02T16:12:22.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454641/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454641/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454641/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-24","Primates: Animal Welfare","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the review of the Code of Practice for the Welfare of Privately Kept Non-Human Primates will commence, and what is the proposed timetable for that review.","false","Biography information for Lord Dholakia",,"Lord Dholakia","HL6391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454642","Department of Health","false","2016-03-08","<p>Public Health England (PHE) collects data on people in prison tested for blood-borne viruses (BBVs) via the Sentinel Surveillance Study. This system does not currently receive reports from all prisons in England where testing occurs currently 28 prisons report data. Table 1 below shows data from this system on the total number of prisoners tested positive for BBVs in the calendar years 2012-2014. Similar information from this study for the year 2015 will not be available until mid-2016. NHS England also collects data on levels of testing for BBVs in prisons via the Health &amp; Justice Indicators of Performance. The numbers of positive tests for BBVs in these data are presented in Table 2 using currently available data. The higher number is due to the greater coverage of prisons by this dataset.</p><p> </p><p>Table 1: Reported levels of positive tests for BBVs for people in prisons for calendar years 2012-14</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>hepatitis B</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>49</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>hepatitis C</p></td><td><p>456</p></td><td><p>400</p></td><td><p>327</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HIV</p></td><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>16</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: PHE Sentinel Surveillance Study</p><p>Table 2: Reported levels of positive tests for BBVs for people in prisons from April 2015 to December 2015</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>April 2015 – December 2015</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>hepatitis B</p></td><td><p>743</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>hepatitis C</p></td><td><p>2164</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HIV</p></td><td><p>1777</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: NHS England</p><p><strong> </strong></p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-03-08T16:23:55.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454642/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454642/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454642/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-24","Screening: Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Prior of Brampton on 9 February (HL5469), of those tested, how many were subsequently diagnosed with (1) hepatitis B, (2) hepatitis C, and (3) HIV, over the same time period.","false","Biography information for Lord Dholakia",,"Lord Dholakia","HL6392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454643","Department of Health","false","2016-03-08","<p>People diagnosed with hepatitis C infection in prison may be treated in prison (through an ‘in-reach’ care programme) or as outpatients via specialist services in National Health Service acute trusts or via a ‘mixed model’. Data on patients treated while in prison or whose treatment is continued following release are held by specialist service providers locally within Operational Delivery Networks and are not currently available centrally.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2016-03-08T16:23:21.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454643/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454643/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454643/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-24","Hepatitis: Prisoners","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many individuals within the total prison estate have commenced treatment for hepatitis C in 2015–16 to date, broken down by Operational Delivery Network area; and of those, how many commenced treatment while in prison but were released from prison before completion of treatment.","false","Biography information for Lord Dholakia",,"Lord Dholakia","HL6393"
