"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454647","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-03-04","<p>We do not hold this information.</p>",,"Lord Freud",,"2016-03-04T14:48:52.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454647/answer","Biography information for Lord Freud","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454647/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-24","British Nationals Abroad: EU Countries","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the financial costs to other EU member states of the social security benefits received by UK nationals resident in those member states.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Leeds",,"The Lord Bishop of Leeds","HL6397"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454648","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-03-09","There are approximately 2 million UK citizens living, working and travelling in the other 27 Member States of the EU. They all currently enjoy a range of specific rights to live, to work and access to pensions, health care and public services that are only guaranteed because of EU law. There would be no requirement under EU law for these rights to be maintained if the UK left the EU. Should an agreement be reached to maintain these rights, the expectation must be that this would have to be reciprocated for EU citizens in the UK.",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2016-03-09T14:13:04.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454648/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454648/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-02-24","EU Countries: British Nationals Abroad","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the implications of a decision by the UK to leave the EU for those UK nationals resident in other EU member states.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Leeds",,"The Lord Bishop of Leeds","HL6398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454649","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-03-02","<p>The current network bandwidth installed on the Queen Elizabeth Class aircraft carriers is sufficient to carry out the endorsed scope of carrier strike operations. As with all programmes, requirements and opportunities are kept under constant review and amended where necessary.</p>",,"Earl Howe",,"2016-03-02T16:38:47.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454649/answer","Biography information for Earl Howe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454649/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-24","Aircraft Carriers: Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Queen Elizabeth class aircraft carriers have sufficient network bandwidth capabilities to make full use of the situational awareness and tactics which the F-35 can offer the Royal Navy; and what plans they have to enhance that use.","false","Biography information for Lord Moonie",,"Lord Moonie","HL6399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454650","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-03-02","<p>If the European Parliament formally endorses the proposal for a revised EU School Milk Scheme in Plenary on 8 March 2016, it is likely to enter into force in spring 2016 and apply in schools from August 2017. We will use this period to consider the new requirements and consult with interested parties. Member States that wish to participate will be obliged to submit a multi-annual national strategy setting out their priorities for implementing the new Scheme. Detailed rules for the drawing up of national strategies will be adopted by the Commission in a delegated act which will be negotiated in the coming months.</p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2016-03-02T15:53:13.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454650/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454650/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-02-24","School Milk","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have (1) to develop a new strategy for the implementation of the European School Milk Scheme from 2017, and (2) to involve stakeholders in developing that strategy.","false","Biography information for Baroness Parminter",,"Baroness Parminter","HL6400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454651","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2016-03-03T17:21:27.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454651/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454651/answer","HL6401 Referral Letter.pdf","HL6401 Referral Letter.pdf","Referral Letter","Referral Letter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454651/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-24","Urban Areas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what was the average growth in Gross Value Added for (1) the English Core Cities, and (2) Liverpool, from 2009 to 2014.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL6401"
