"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454038","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-07","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>When the apprenticeships levy is introduced in April 2017, small and medium sized employers will continue to have access to government funding to support apprenticeships. We will provide further details on the support available later this year.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-07T14:26:45.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454038/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454038/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the apprenticeship levy on the training requirements of small and medium-sized firms unable to access the levy.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","28100"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454039","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The combination of the apprenticeship levy, the protection of the Adult Education Budget and the extension of loans mean that by 2019-20 the total spending power of the FE sector to support participation will be £3.41bn, an increase in cash terms of 40% compared with 2015-16.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-02T17:57:55.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454039/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454039/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the apprenticeship levy on training and skills funding for people aged over 21.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","28101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454040","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>We are not cutting business support mechanisms to implement the levy. We are improving our business services by developing the Digital Apprenticeship Service.</p><p> </p><p>Through this online mechanism employers will have access to a number of services to help them choose and pay for apprenticeship training in a simple way.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-02T17:11:29.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454040/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454040/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether his Department intends to cease any existing or planned business support mechanisms in order to implement the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","28102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454041","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>The final size and structure of the Institute for Apprenticeships will be determined by the shadow chair and CEO later in the spring and this will then determine its final running cost. The body will be funded by Government using public funds, as the rest of the governance system is, and it is expected that some funding will be freed up from savings across the Department.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-02T17:22:11.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454041/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454041/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","Institute of Apprenticeships: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the estimated (a) cost of establishing and (b) annual running cost of the Institute of Apprenticeships is; whether his Department has made an assessment of the effects of funding that institute on his Department's annual programme budget; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","28157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454042","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>HM Treasury published a Tax Information and Impact Note on 4 February 2016 at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeship-levy/apprenticeship-levy" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/apprenticeship-levy/apprenticeship-levy</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-03-02T17:19:13.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454042/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454042/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish his Department's impact assessment of the apprenticeship levy.","false","Biography information for Mr Iain Wright","Hartlepool","Mr Iain Wright","28103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454043","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Government's view is that the UK will be stronger, safer and better off in a reformed European Union.</p><p>As required by the EU Referendum Act 2015, the Government is committed to producing clear information, ahead of the Referendum, on: the outcome of the renegotiation, rights and obligations in European Union law, an assessment of alternatives to membership, and the process for leaving.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2016-02-29T14:58:31.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454043/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454043/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","UK Membership of EU: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential implications for projects supported by State Aid agreements of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","28116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454044","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>Information on the number of enquiries to the Pay and Work Rights Helpline or Acas by workers from the ‘domiciliary care’ and ‘residential care’ sector is not available. The answer of 11 February 2016 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-02-03/25610/" target="_blank">25610</a> represents the most detailed breakdown of trade sector information available.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","28164","2016-03-02T11:00:33.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454044/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454044/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","ACAS: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 11 February 2016 to Question 25610, how many national minimum wage enquiries were made to (a) the Pay and Work Rights Helpline and (b) Acas between 2009-10 and 2014-15 by (i) domiciliary and (ii) residential care workers.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","28163"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454045","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-03-02","<p>Information on the number of enquiries to the Pay and Work Rights Helpline or Acas by workers from the ‘domiciliary care’ and ‘residential care’ sector is not available. The answer of 11 February 2016 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2016-02-03/25610/" target="_blank">25610</a> represents the most detailed breakdown of trade sector information available.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","28163","2016-03-02T11:00:33.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454045/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454045/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-02-23","ACAS: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, pursuant to the Answer of 11 February 2016 to Question 25610, how many national minimum wage enquiries relating to non-payment or deductions were made to (a) the Pay and Work Rights Helpline and (b) Acas by people working in (i) domiciliary and (ii) residential care between 2009-10 and 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","28164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454046","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-26","<p>All civil servants are subject to the requirements of the Civil Service Code and Civil Service Management Code. Further guidance on attendance at external events including those organised by political parties can be found in the Directory of Civil Service Guidance (vol 2).</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","28062","2016-02-26T13:59:47.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454046/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454046/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Senior Civil Servants: Political Impartiality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what guidance his Department issues to senior civil servants attending events organised by hon. Members of the Government party.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454047","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-29","<p>Cabinet Office officials undertook several discussions with DCLG on this matter. The discussions were varied, extensive and frequent, and covered both development and implementation.</p><p> </p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-29T13:53:36.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454047/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454047/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Department for Communities and Local Government: Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what discussions his Department has had with the Department for Communities and Local Government on the applicability of that Department's anti-sock puppet clause pilot scheme to other departments.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","28159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454048","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The few representations received about implementation of the new clause in Government grants have given us the opportunity to explain that the clause does not stop grant recipients from lobbying, but prevents them from spending government grant funded by taxpayers given for a different purpose on lobbying.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-03-03T13:13:56.65Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454048/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454048/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what representations he has received outlining concerns related to his Department's new anti-lobbying policy.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","28110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454049","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-26","<p>All civil servants are subject to the requirements of the Civil Service Code and Civil Service Management Code. Further guidance on attendance at external events including those organised by political parties can be found in the Directory of Civil Service Guidance (vol 2).</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","28063","2016-02-26T13:59:47.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454049/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454049/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Senior Civil Servants: Political Impartiality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what guidance his Department provides to senior civil servants on speaking at public events.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454050","Department of Health","false","2016-02-26","<p>We welcome the recommendations for government in the report and will be considering how best to integrate them into our work programme. There will be an impact on policies across Government in this period and, more importantly, a positive impact on people using mental health services.</p><p><br> The Mental Health Five Year Forward View Taskforce Report proposes, and we accept, investing over £1 billion of additional funding by 2020/21 to reach one million more people. There are a number of recommendations in the report which will have an impact on crisis care services, accident and emergency departments, mothers suffering from mental health problems, suicide prevention, children and young people’s mental health services, access to psychological therapies and the physical health of people with mental health problems. The £1 billion announced with the Taskforce report is the total annual cost for all areas in 2020/21.</p><p> </p><p>Announcements on the development of policies, including those with reference to implementing the Mental Health Taskforce will be made in due course.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-02-26T09:29:33.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454050/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454050/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-02-23","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the implications for the policies of the Cabinet Office of the recommendations of the Mental Health Taskforce report, published in February 2016.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","28085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454051","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Electoral Commission provides detailed guidance to Electoral Registration Officers on access and supply of the full electoral register, including by credit reference agencies.</p><p>The regulations on the supply of electoral roll data to credit reference agencies are set out in The Representation of the People (England and Wales)(Amendment) Regulations 2002. Under Regulation 114, credit reference agencies registered under Part III of the Consumer Credit Act and carrying on the business of providing credit reference services may only use the full electoral register for specified purposes; namely for checking a person’s identity if they apply for credit, and for the prevention of money laundering fraud. Electoral Registration Officers are entitled to charge credit reference agencies a small fee for copies of the full register, to cover administration costs.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-02-29T14:01:20.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454051/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454051/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Electoral Register: Credit Reference Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what (a) guidance his Department issues and (b) regulations are in place on the provision of electoral roll data to credit reference agencies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28021"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454052","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-01","<p>Under the Regulation 115 of the Representation of the People (England and Wales)(Amendment) Regulations 2002, anyone who is supplied with the full register is not permitted to sell a copy to any person, disclose any information contained in it, or use it for anything apart from the specified purpose for which the full register has been supplied. In contravening this provision, a person would be guilty of an offence and liable on summary conviction to a fine not exceeding level 5 on the standard scale, which currently stands at £5000.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-03-01T11:09:35.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454052/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454052/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Electoral Register: Credit Reference Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what checks his Department has in place to ensure that credit reference firms do not sell-on electoral roll data.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454053","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-01","<p>Available records show that in the last calendar year the Cabinet Office received one letter of complaint about access to the electoral register by credit reference agencies, and nine letters of complaint about the sale of the edited electoral register.</p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-03-01T10:38:07.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454053/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454053/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Electoral Register: Credit Reference Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many complaints his Department has received on the sale of electoral roll data by credit reference firms.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28019"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454054","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-01","<p>The Information Commissioner’s Office provides guidance to both private and public sector organisations to help them understand their obligations under the Data Protection Act. Organisations wishing to process personal data in the UK, including credit reference agencies, must register with the ICO and comply with the DPA’s eight data protection principles. Among other things, these principles require personal data to be processed fairly and lawfully; to be accurate and up-to-date; not to be kept for longer than is necessary; and to be processed in accordance with the rights of the data subjects under the DPA.</p><p> </p><p>The ICO’s website provides public information on credit reference agencies’ use of the electoral register at (<a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/credit/" target="_blank">https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/credit/</a>).</p><p> </p>","Weston-super-Mare","John Penrose",,"2016-03-01T10:37:13.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454054/answer","Biography information for John Penrose","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454054/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Electoral Register: Credit Reference Agencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what guidance his Department issues to credit reference firms on handling data on people who are on the closed electoral register.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","28020"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454055","Cabinet Office","false","2016-02-29","<p>The Code of Conduct for Special Advisers sets out the role of special advisers and describes the range of activities they may undertake. Copies of the Code of Conduct are available in the Libraries of the House and on-line at</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/468340/CODE_OF_CONDUCT_FOR_SPECIAL_ADVISERS_-_15_OCTOBER_2015_FINAL.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/468340/CODE_OF_CONDUCT_FOR_SPECIAL_ADVISERS_-_15_OCTOBER_2015_FINAL.pdf</a></p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock",,"2016-02-29T14:09:18.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454055/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454055/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Cabinet Office: Ministerial Policy Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the (a) policy and (b) other responsibilities are of each special adviser in his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","27946"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454056","Cabinet Office","false","2016-03-03","<p>The Cabinet Office takes the well-being of its employees seriously and provides a range of support, including the recent launch of the Cabinet Office Listening Service, resourced by staff who have been trained in active listening and emotional support. The service can provide upfront support to Cabinet Office staff dealing directly or indirectly with specific issues in their personal or working life or to help them to cope with mental health issues of any kind including depression, anxiety or stress. Listeners can also signpost individuals onto other relevant services such as the external Employee Assistant Programme which offers counselling, impartial advice and access to online health and wellness related resources.</p><p>The department has established an employee led WorkWell community to further develop and implement a strategy for wellness. Progress to date includes establishing resilience training for senior leaders and their teams, signing up to the Time to Change pledge on mental health, providing access to coaching and training in skills to improve wellbeing such as mindfulness. WorkWell are also seeking to increase awareness of opportunities to improve physical wellbeing at work including provision of on-site health checks.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","27939","2016-03-03T13:18:21.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454056/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454056/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-02-23","Cabinet Office: Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what his Department's wellness strategy is.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","27925"
