"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454058","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-02","<p>The latest regional public sector employment survey figures are available online at: http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/pse/public-sector-employment/q3-2015/index.html, the figures for Barnsley and Barnsley East can be found in the Annual Population Survey (Oct 2014-Sep 2015): https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/default.asp.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-03-02T16:47:25.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454058/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454058/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-23","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many publicly-funded jobs relating directly to the Northern Powerhouse there are in (a) Barnsley East constituency, (b) Barnsley, (c) Yorkshire and the Humber, (d) London and (e) other regions of England.","false","Biography information for Michael Dugher","Barnsley East","Michael Dugher","27880"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454059","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) opened 216 interventions under IR35 in the year 2013/14 and 199 in the year 2014/15. HMRC has increased the number of IR35 inquiries in recent years and has at least 250 open at any one time.</p><p>The Government published a discussion document on 17 July 2015, inviting views on options for reforming IR35. The discussion period closed on 30 September and the Government will announce next steps in due course.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-02-26T12:19:24.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454059/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454059/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-23","Tax Avoidance: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many investigations have been opened by HM Revenue and Customs under IR35 in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","27858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454060","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-02-26","<p>The Information requested is not routinely recorded for management information purposes and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p>Research from 2013 shows that between nine and ten per cent of automatically enrolled workers had opted out of their pension scheme. Our latest figures show that since the roll out of automatic enrolment, nearly 6 million people have now been automatically enrolled, and opt outs have remained much lower than were originally anticipated. We expect that around nine million workers will be newly saving or saving more by 2018. The Department is doing further analysis into workplace pension participation and opt out rates.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-02-26T15:11:54.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454060/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454060/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-02-23","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people automatically enrolled into workplace pensions between October 2012 and October 2013 have since withdrawn from that scheme.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","27859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454061","HM Treasury","false","2016-03-11","<p>The Government’s new settlement means that EU nationals whose children live abroad will ultimately receive Child Benefit at a rate that reflects the conditions – including the standard of living and child benefit paid – of the country where their child lives. This will restore fairness to the system.</p><p> </p><p>Savings relating to the indexation of Child Benefit will be confirmed once the rates have been finalised.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","27852 ; 27853","2016-03-11T12:34:02.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454061/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454061/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-23","Child Benefit: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the savings to the public purse of the proposed reduction of child benefits paid overseas.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","27861"
