"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454102","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-01","<p>Arts Council England (ACE) assesses all applications for funding against the specific criteria for each programme, as well as one or more of its 5 goals of excellence, opportunity, resilience, leadership and young people. ACE investment in theatre over the last 3 years is:<br>£136,024,252 in 2013/14; £148,745,455 in 2014/15; and £138,018,756 to date (23 Feb 2016) in 2015/16.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-03-01T16:11:19.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454102/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454102/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-23","Theatre: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what criteria Arts Council England uses to allocate funding to theatre companies; and how much such funding has been disbursed to theatre companies in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","28089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454103","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-03-02","<p>The two national events that marked the centenary of the battle of Gallipoli on 24th and 25th Apri 2015, were key commemorative events in the centenary programme.</p><p> </p><p>The first, a UK-led Commonwealth and Ireland Ceremony was held at the Commonwealth War Graves Commission’s Helles Memorial in Turkey on 24 April 2015, the eve of the centenary of the Gallipoli landings. This event was attended by The Prince of Wales, accompanied by Prince Harry, senior representatives of the nations involved in the Gallipoi Campaign and descendants. The Prince of Wales met with descendants on board the Royal Navy’s ship HMS Bulwark.</p><p> </p><p>The second, on Anzac Day, was held at the Cenotaph in Whitehall. This National Service of Commemoration event was attended by Her Majesty The Queen, senior representatives of the participant nations, and around 2500 descendants, included wreath-laying and a march past the Cenotaph led by military personnel.</p>","Bexleyheath and Crayford","David Evennett",,"2016-03-02T11:19:51.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454103/answer","Biography information for Sir David Evennett","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454103/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-23","World War I: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what plans the Government has to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the Battle of Gallipoli.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","28090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454104","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-02-26","<p>In its 2015 publication Connected Nations, Ofcom estimated that 68% of SMEs had access to superfast broadband in May 2015, and almost half (around 130,000) in certain business areas were unable to receive speeds above 10Mbit/s.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is supporting investment to provide superfast broadband coverage to 90% of UK premises by early 2016 and 95% by December 2017. In addition, BDUK's Connection Voucher Scheme issued around 55,000 vouchers to businesses to enable to access Superfast broadband. However, this does not include the provision of leased lines which offer an alternative connectivity option for businesses.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2016-02-26T10:21:08.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454104/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454104/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-02-23","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment (a) his Department and (b) Ofcom has made of the number of (a) business parks which do not have superfast broadband and (b) businesses based in business parks which do not have superfast broadband.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","28131"
