"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454106","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>Information is not available in the format requested. However, in May 2009 a total of 130 Vector vehicles were in operational use in Iraq and Afghanistan. Vector was withdrawn from use on operational tasks in 2009.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-29T16:54:44.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454106/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454106/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454106/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-23","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Vector protected vehicles were in operational use by the army in each year since 2007.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28120"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454107","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>Vector was finally removed from service in 2015 and is currently awaiting disposal. Protected mobility capability is currently provided by a range of vehicles from the existing core fleet, including former Urgent Operational Requirement platforms retained in service following their return from Afghanistan. In the longer term, the Multi Role Vehicle (Protected) series of platforms will provide a light to medium protected vehicle capability.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-29T17:48:54.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454107/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454107/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454107/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-23","Armoured Fighting Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his policy is on replacement of Vector protected patrol vehicles.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28121"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454108","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-29","<p>The number of equipment failure reports filed for each vehicle is included within the table below. These totals are for all failures reported to the Equipment Failure Reporting System; this will include reports raised incorrectly or unnecessarily. Totals are from 1 January to 31 December each year.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2010</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2011</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2013</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Combat</strong></p></td><td colspan="6"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Challenger 2</p></td><td><p>880</p></td><td><p>686</p></td><td><p>431</p></td><td><p>976</p></td><td><p>1421</p></td><td><p>1708</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Warrior</p></td><td><p>535</p></td><td><p>551</p></td><td><p>518</p></td><td><p>803</p></td><td><p>1009</p></td><td><p>1583</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Protected Patrol</strong></p></td><td colspan="6"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cougar variants[1]</p></td><td><p>480</p></td><td><p>497</p></td><td><p>1018</p></td><td><p>1067</p></td><td><p>293</p></td><td><p>321</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Foxhound</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>N/A</p></td><td><p>609</p></td><td><p>621</p></td><td><p>528</p></td><td><p>1179</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Landrover Variants</p></td><td><p>98</p></td><td><p>245</p></td><td><p>391</p></td><td><p>857</p></td><td><p>1559</p></td><td><p>1011</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Vector</p></td><td><p>35</p></td><td><p>36</p></td><td><p>21</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Reconnaissance</strong></p></td><td colspan="6"><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>CVR(T)</p></td><td><p>393</p></td><td><p>292</p></td><td><p>346</p></td><td><p>260</p></td><td><p>722</p></td><td><p>862</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jackal</p></td><td><p>560</p></td><td><p>636</p></td><td><p>781</p></td><td><p>561</p></td><td><p>458</p></td><td><p>151</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>These figures reflect an increase in platform usage rates as the Army redeployed from operations in Afghanistan (where primarily Cougar variant Protected Patrol Vehicles and Jackal reconnaissance vehicles were used) to training on Challenger 2, Warrior, CVR(T), and Landrover vehicles. Equipment Failure Reports are raised for a wide range of fault types (from minor to major) and also for routine part replacement.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Cougar Variants comprise Mastiff, Ridgback and Wolfhound</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-02-29T17:58:26.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454108/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454108/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-23","Armed Forces: Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many equipment failure reports were filed for each type of (a) combat vehicle, (b) protected patrol vehicle and (c) reconnaissance vehicle in each of the last six years.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","28119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454109","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-02-26","<p>From 2 December 2015 till 23 February 2016 there have been a total of 362 strikes against Daesh targets. Of these 319 have taken place in Iraq and 43 in Syria.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2016-02-26T14:23:58.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454109/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454109/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/454109/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-02-23","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many RAF airstrikes have taken place against Daesh targets in (a) Iraq and (b) Syria since 2 December 2015.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","28134"
